               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nWhen we consecutively add the same value—that is, when we multiply numbers (<htcite0>)—we may end up changing the order of the factors, depending on the numbers we are working with. To better understand these changes, we recommend studying the entire chapter on multiplication tables in the *First Steps* section, as well as the text on rereading numbers (<htcite1>; <htcite2>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eaa59295-fb80-4c33-b1e4-bcdf3c11dabf",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Adding the same number",
