         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nAs Dhavit Prem rightly points out in one of his presentations on the Inca Yupana, one of the problems people face during the learning process is the fear of making mistakes (<htcite0>), even though mistakes are part of that process.\n\nOne possible explanation for this fear of error may lie in the fact that, from an early age, we do not fully understand what we are studying. Thus, we fail to realize that the very process of studying can indicate whether we are on the right track or whether we have gone wrong at some point, which can naturally lead us to make mistakes.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "5dbd2e9f-5631-407e-9b80-e3a5d4f8838f",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "00:16:21, 02:09:08",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2026",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: On Mistakes</b><br /><br />Would you like mathematical calculations, at the very least, to tell you whether the path you are following is right or wrong?</div></div></center></p>",
